<collectorName id="26CE5379FFD8FFA5FF43F881FF00F8DB" box="[136,203,1808,1834]" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">When</collectorName>
describing 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D2CFFD8FFA5FE98F880FD0DF8DA" authority=", Schumann (1886)" authorityName=", Schumann" authorityYear="1886" box="[339,710,1808,1835]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="1" pageNumber="181" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="conwentzii">
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFD8FFA5FE98F880FE20F8DB" box="[339,491,1809,1834]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">L. conwentzii</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFD8FFA5FE37F881FD0DF8DA" author="Schumann, K." box="[508,710,1808,1835]" pageId="1" pageNumber="181" pagination="117 - 200" refId="ref8376" refString="Schumann, K. (1886) Tilliaceae. Flora Brasiliensis, enumeratio plantarum in Brasilia hactenus detectarum: quas suis aliorumque botanicorum studiis descriptas et methodo naturali digestas partim icone illustratas 12 (3): 117 - 200. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 454" type="journal article" year="1886">Schumann (1886)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
cited two collections in the protologue, 
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFD8FFA5FB57F881FADCF8DB" box="[1180,1303,1808,1834]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">
<collectorName id="26CE5379FFD8FFA5FB57F881FB2FF8DB" box="[1180,1252,1808,1834]" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">Riedel</collectorName>
107
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFD8FFA5FA98F881FF07F8BF" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">
<collectorName id="26CE5379FFD8FFA5FA98F881FA67F8DB" box="[1363,1452,1808,1834]" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">Glaziou</collectorName>
11795
</emphasis>
, which are 
<typeStatus id="5480880DFFD8FFA5FE9FF8A4FE72F8BE" box="[340,441,1845,1871]" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">syntypes</typeStatus>
, therefore, in accordance with 
<collectorName id="26CE5379FFD8FFA5FCD1F8A5FC8CF8BF" box="[794,839,1844,1870]" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">Art.</collectorName>
9.3 of the ICN, it is maybe select a 
<typeStatus id="5480880DFFD8FFA5FB27F8A5FA9DF8BF" box="[1260,1366,1844,1870]" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">lectotype</typeStatus>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFD8FFA5FAA9F8A5FF18F882" author="Cunha, M. C. S." pageId="1" pageNumber="181" pagination="5 - 41" refId="ref7419" refString="Cunha, M. C. S. (1985) Revisao das especies do genero Luehea Willd. (Tiliaceae), ocorrentes no estado do Rio de Janeiro. Sellowia, Anais Botanicos do Herbario Barbosa Rodrigues 37: 5 - 41." type="journal article" year="1985">
<collectingCountry id="F32C763FFFD8FFA5FAA9F8A5FA60F8BF" box="[1378,1451,1844,1870]" name="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">Cunha</collectingCountry>
(1985)
</bibRefCitation>
designated 
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFD8FFA5FE9CF8C9FE04F883" box="[343,463,1880,1906]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">
<collectorName id="26CE5379FFD8FFA5FE9CF8C9FE54F883" box="[343,415,1880,1906]" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">Riedel</collectorName>
<quantity id="4CC39B4AFFD8FFA5FE6EF8C9FE04F883" box="[421,463,1880,1906]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7178" pageId="1" pageNumber="181" unit="in" value="107.0">107</quantity>
</emphasis>
in LE as the type, but no specimen has ever been found in this herbarium (
<collectorName id="26CE5379FFD8FFA5FAC4F8C9FA63F883" box="[1295,1448,1880,1906]" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">L. Averyanov</collectorName>
, pers. comm.). 
<collectorName id="26CE5379FFD8FFA5FEE4F8ECFE9DF866" box="[303,342,1917,1943]" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">For</collectorName>
this reason, we herein designate 
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFD8FFA5FD11F8EDFC9DF867" box="[730,854,1916,1942]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">
<collectorName id="26CE5379FFD8FFA5FD11F8EDFCE9F867" box="[730,802,1916,1942]" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">Riedel</collectorName>
107
</emphasis>
(
<accessionNumber id="9468AB4CFFD8FFA5FCACF8EDFC2FF866" box="[871,996,1916,1943]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/BR549139" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">BR549139</accessionNumber>
) as the 
<typeStatus id="5480880DFFD8FFA5FB88F8EDFB61F867" box="[1091,1194,1916,1942]" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">lectotype</typeStatus>
by choosing the most complete and preserved specimen. 
<location id="8EE46074FFD8FFA5FDEBF831FDAFF84B" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:039287B9FFD8FFA5FF43F9AAFD57F82F:8EE46074FFD8FFA5FDEBF831FDAFF84B" box="[544,612,1952,1978]" country="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" name="Based" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">Based</location>
on 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B5EFFD8FFA5FD5CF831FCFEF84A" author="Cunha, M. C. S." box="[663,821,1952,1979]" pageId="1" pageNumber="181" pagination="5 - 41" refId="ref7419" refString="Cunha, M. C. S. (1985) Revisao das especies do genero Luehea Willd. (Tiliaceae), ocorrentes no estado do Rio de Janeiro. Sellowia, Anais Botanicos do Herbario Barbosa Rodrigues 37: 5 - 41." type="journal article" year="1985">
<collectingCountry id="F32C763FFFD8FFA5FD5CF831FD2BF84B" box="[663,736,1952,1978]" name="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">Cunha</collectingCountry>
(1985)
</bibRefCitation>
and the present study, the application of the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C3B4D2CFFD8FFA5FA5EF830FECBF82F" authorityName=", Schumann" authorityYear="1886" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="1" pageNumber="181" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="conwentzii">
<emphasis id="B94FEABDFFD8FFA5FA5EF830FECBF82F" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="181">L. conwentzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is confirmed as an accepted species.
</paragraph>
